# Progression Systems

## Applies when

Apply when creating, reviewing, or modifying contracts, Street Deals, debts, contacts, Turf Levels, their Resources, owner hooks, facade methods, UI progression views, or related tests. Priority: Critical.

## Source of truth

- `docs/prd/09_CONTRACTS.md` owns contracts.
- `docs/prd/10_STREET_DEALS_AND_DEBTS.md` owns Street Deals and debts.
- `docs/prd/11_CONTACTS.md` owns contacts.
- `docs/prd/12_TURF_LEVELS.md` owns Turf Levels.
- `docs/prd/21_OPEN_QUESTIONS_AND_FIXES.md` owns accepted `FIX-*` decisions and open ambiguity handling.

This rule is a guardrail routing summary for progression systems. It must not override PRD 09-12 or accepted `FIX-*` decisions. If any listed value, state owner, hook, event, timing, or behavior conflicts with the owner PRD or an accepted `FIX-*`, stop and report PRD drift.

## Routing

- Route contract behavior to `09_CONTRACTS.md` and `ContractLogic.gd`.
- Route Street Deal and debt behavior to `10_STREET_DEALS_AND_DEBTS.md`, `StreetDealLogic.gd`, and `DebtLogic.gd`.
- Route contact behavior to `11_CONTACTS.md` and `ContactLogic.gd`.
- Route Turf Level behavior to `12_TURF_LEVELS.md` and `TurfLevelLogic.gd`.
- Route canonical IDs, errors, and event payloads to `03_IDS_AND_CONSTANTS.md`.
- Route runtime shapes and ownership to `04_GAME_STATE_SCHEMA.md`.
- Route facade payload/result/signal behavior to `16_GAME_STATE_MANAGER_API.md`.

Progression modules may invoke owner-defined hook entry points across systems, but must not implement another owner module's internal rules.

## State ownership

Use only these canonical owners:

| Runtime concept | Canonical owner |
| --- | --- |
| Contract offer IDs | `state["contract_offer_ids"]` |
| Selected contract ID | `state["selected_contract_id"]` |
| Runtime contracts | `player["contracts"]` |
| Global Street Deal offer/event state | `state["street_deals"]` |
| Debts | `player["debts"]` |
| Owned contacts, cooldowns, usage | `player["contacts"]` |
| Pending contact offer | `state["contacts"]["pending_offer"]` |
| Turf Level | integer `state["turf_level"]` |
| Turf runtime flags | `player["turf_flags"]` |
| Temporary modifiers | `player["temporary_modifiers"]` |

- Do not duplicate ownership in aliases such as `contract_offers`, root `contracts`, `active_contract`, `active_debts`, `player["street_deals"]`, root unlocked-contact arrays, string Turf IDs, or territory IDs.
- `GameStateValidator` must reject aliases, extra keys, invalid IDs, wrong types, and invalid event payloads.

## Contracts

- MVP contracts apply only to the human player.
- AI players must not receive contracts.
- Setup contract preview returns exactly 3 deterministic unique contract IDs and mutates no active state, active random, runtime contract, or gameplay log.
- Committed setup regenerates the same 3 offers, validates selected membership, stores `state["contract_offer_ids"]`, stores `state["selected_contract_id"]`, creates exactly one human runtime contract in `player["contracts"]`, and commits atomically.
- Contract completion does not apply the reward automatically.
- Rewards apply only through `claim_contract`.
- Repeated claim must fail.
- Completed contracts can be claimed after deadline.
- Incomplete contracts fail only when `round > deadline`.
- Deadline round itself is still valid for completion.
- Completed contracts must not later become failed.
- Contract failure reasons are exactly `war_played` and `deadline_exceeded`.
- Every first failure appends the canonical `CONTRACT_FAILED` event.
- Contract logic must not resolve purchases, Income, combat, Street Deals, AI behavior, phase flow, or UI behavior.

Use only owner-defined hooks:

- `MarketLogic` calls contract purchase hooks after successful purchase and placement.
- `IncomeLogic` calls contract hooks after Income, Cops upkeep, and debt processing.
- `CombatEngine` calls contract hooks after valid resolved attacks, with success-specific progress only after unblocked success.
- `GamePhaseController` calls deadline/failure checks at round start and phase checkpoints.
- `StreetDealLogic` calls contract state-change hooks after successful Street Deal effects where relevant.

## Street Deals and debts

- Street Deals occur only after Action in rounds 4, 8, and 12.
- In MVP, only the human chooses Street Deal options.
- AI players do not choose Street Deals.
- AI may receive explicit Street Deal side effects only where owner PRD defines them.
- `choices_by_player` normally stores only `player_1`.
- Street Deal generation is deterministic and must use unified `state["random"]`.
- Used deals must not repeat in the same run.
- Active debt blocks only `loan_shark`; other Street Deals remain available.
- `loan_shark` creates debts in `player["debts"]`.
- Debts are processed during Income after income gain and Cops upkeep, before contract hooks.
- Manual debt repayment is not MVP unless the owner PRD changes it.
- Debt penalties and repayment behavior are owned only by `DebtLogic`.
- `dirty_tip` Option B selects AI target through `SeededPicker` from `ai_1`, `ai_2`, `ai_3`.
- `risky_contract` Option B chooses richest AI by highest Nal; ties use stable order `ai_1`, `ai_2`, `ai_3`; no random is used.
- `inside_contact` Option A calls `ContactLogic` to generate a deterministic 2-contact offer; `StreetDealLogic` must not directly unlock contacts.
- Turf Level 8 increases only direct upfront human Street Deal payments by +1. It must not affect debt amount due, debt penalties, future debt repayment, positive Nal gains, or AI side effects.

## Contacts

- In MVP, only the human can unlock, own, select, or activate contacts.
- AI players must not receive contact offers or contacts.
- Human may own at most 1 contact.
- Existing contacts cannot be replaced in MVP.
- Owned contacts are stored only in `player["contacts"]`.
- Pending offers are stored only in `state["contacts"]["pending_offer"]`.
- Contact offers must be deterministic and use unified `state["random"]`.
- `inside_contact` always requests 2 contact options.
- Strong AI victory normally requests 3 contact options, or 2 at Turf Level 7+.
- Strong AI victory means the human successfully and unblocked destroys a strong AI Status building: `stash`, `workshop`, or `district_control`.
- Blocked attacks, failed validation, Nal steal, Engine destruction, non-strong AI targets, and AI attackers must not create a strong-AI-victory contact offer.
- `black_cash` is passive and changes Brothel double bonus from +5 to +6 through owner Income flow.
- `corrupt_clerk` is passive; its first Status discount is consumed only after successful Status purchase.
- `street_medic` prevents only 1 VP loss from debt penalty once per run through the debt hook. It does not prevent Nal loss and is not consumed when effective VP loss is 0.

## Turf Levels

- Turf Level is selected manually before the run.
- Turf Level is an integer in `TurfLevelIds.ALL`, valid range `0..10`.
- String Turf IDs, territory IDs, and automatic Turf progression are forbidden in MVP.
- Turf Level must not change during a match.
- Turf Levels are cumulative: level `N` applies effects from `1..N`.
- Turf Level Resources and `effect_summary` are display/config data; gameplay must not parse text summaries.

Owner routing for cumulative effects:

| Level | Effect | Runtime owner |
| ---: | --- | --- |
| 1 | All AI start with +1 Nal | setup / `TurfLevelLogic` |
| 2 | Strong AI starts with +1 VP | setup / AI + Turf integration |
| 3 | Human starts with -1 Nal after role, minimum 3 | setup / `TurfLevelLogic` |
| 4 | Rotating market has 3 cards instead of 4 | `MarketLogic` |
| 5 | Human Cops upkeep interval is 2 instead of 3 | `IncomeLogic` |
| 6 | First AI War purchase each round costs 1 less | `PriceLogic` / `TurfLevelLogic` |
| 7 | Strong AI victory contact offer count is 2 instead of 3 | `ContactLogic` |
| 8 | Direct upfront human Street Deal payments increase by +1 | `StreetDealLogic` |
| 9 | AI War purchase weight +20% only if human strictly leads VP | `AIPurchaseLogic` |
| 10 | AI wins VP tie if AI is among leaders | `WinnerResolver` / `TurfLevelLogic` |

- Level 6 discount applies only to AI War purchases and consumes only after successful purchase.
- Level 9 must not mutate AI profile Resources.
- Level 10 winner tie-break must not use random. If multiple AI are tied, choose highest Nal, then stable order `ai_1`, `ai_2`, `ai_3`.

## FIX decisions to enforce

Follow these accepted decisions exactly:

- `FIX-001`: Human chooses Street Deals; AI only receives explicit side effects.
- `FIX-002` and `FIX-030`: `state["street_deals"]` owns global Street Deal state; debts are in `player["debts"]`.
- `FIX-003`: Active debt blocks only `loan_shark`.
- `FIX-004`: Turf Level 8 affects only direct upfront human Street Deal payments.
- `FIX-005`: `dirty_tip` Option B random AI target uses deterministic `SeededPicker`.
- `FIX-006`: `risky_contract` Option B richest-AI tie uses stable AI order, no random.
- `FIX-007`: `inside_contact` creates a ContactLogic offer; StreetDealLogic does not unlock contacts directly.
- `FIX-008`: owned contacts are in `player["contacts"]`; pending offers are in `state["contacts"]["pending_offer"]`.
- `FIX-009`: max 1 contact means no replacement.
- `FIX-010`: strong AI victory means unblocked human destruction of strong AI Status building.
- `FIX-011`: strong AI victory offers 3 contacts normally, 2 at Turf Level 7+; `inside_contact` remains 2.
- `FIX-012`: `corrupt_clerk` consumes only after successful Status purchase.
- `FIX-013`: Turf Level 10 multiple AI tie-break uses highest Nal, then stable AI order.
- `FIX-031`: canonical keys, IDs, errors, and event payloads only; no free-form nested result dictionaries in events.
- `FIX-033`: contract setup is pure deterministic 3-offer preview, then validated atomic commit.

## Forbidden behavior

- Do not duplicate source-of-truth ownership across root state, player state, Resources, UI, or facade caches.
- Do not give contracts to AI players.
- Do not give AI players Street Deal choices.
- Do not give contacts to AI players.
- Do not replace an existing contact.
- Do not change Turf Level during a match.
- Do not implement automatic Turf Level progression in MVP.
- Do not use string Turf/territory IDs.
- Do not auto-claim contract rewards.
- Do not let completed contracts fail after deadline.
- Do not make active debt block all Street Deals.
- Do not store debts globally as `active_debts`.
- Do not unlock contacts directly from StreetDealLogic.
- Do not implement contract/contact/debt/Turf internals inside another owner module.
- Do not parse Resource descriptions or effect summaries as gameplay logic.
- Do not invent event payloads, validation errors, fallback strings, hooks, rewards, deadlines, debt penalties, contact effects, or Turf effects.
- Do not use forbidden random APIs; deterministic offers and random side effects must use the owner deterministic random contract.

## Required behavior

- Use only owner-defined hooks and result shapes.
- Apply accepted `FIX-*` decisions before older PRD text.
- Validate exact canonical state keys and reject aliases.
- Keep progression Resources immutable.
- Commit through `GameStateManager` facade transactions.
- Failed validation must not mutate active state, random, logs, player resources, contracts, debts, contacts, Turf flags, or pending offers.
- Add or update focused GUT tests when progression behavior changes.
- If owner PRD and accepted `FIX-*` conflict, stop and report PRD drift instead of choosing silently.
- If behavior is absent or ambiguous, reference an existing `OQ-*`; if none exists, report the proposed `OQ-*` instead of inventing behavior.

## Required tests

Progression tests must cover:

- deterministic contract offer preview and committed setup membership;
- human-only contract selection and AI contract rejection;
- contract completion, deadline, claim, repeated claim, and failure mutation safety;
- Street Deal timing, deterministic generation, human-only choice, used-deal exclusion, and active-debt `loan_shark` filtering;
- debt storage in `player["debts"]`, automatic Income processing, repayment, overdue penalties, VP clamp, and `street_medic` hook;
- contact ownership split, deterministic offers, max 1 contact, no replacement, strong AI victory offers, and selection mutation safety;
- Turf Level range, cumulative effects, setup modifiers, per-level owner integrations, no match-time Turf changes, and Level 10 tie-break;
- static scans for UI-owned progression logic, forbidden random APIs, duplicate ownership aliases, and untracked ambiguity markers.

